Arrays is a utility we have to import it from JRE
Arrays.toString() - will print out an array in a string format
Arrays.sort () => will print out content of Array in accending order

int [] num= {5,7,9,5,4,2,3};
Arrays.sort(num);
num={2,3,4,5,5,7,9}

to make it descending order:
Arrays.sort(nums);
int [] arrDesc= new int[num.length]; new array thats exact same size as num array
int k=0- created to store a new descending array list of nums
                         i>=0 it means it   will stop at index 0
for(int i=num.length()-1;i>=0; i--){
arrDesc[k]=arr[i];
k++;
} sout (Arrays.toString(arrDesc));


